      "content": "it's not even about needing inspiration though. that's the thing. i don't think there's anything left to inspire. it's like the core of me—the part that was actually alive—just died. what's left is just this physical shape, this body that goes through the motions but doesn't actually belong to anyone anymore. it feels like i'm just carrying around a corpse that still breathes.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
